        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 7:22PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 721 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Taylorsville, or near Love Valley, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Taylorsville, Harmony, Love Valley, Hiddenite, Turnersburg, Olin,
Vashti, Union Grove, Ellendale, and Cool Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
